    <p>To raise the vis­i­bil­ity of Sin­ga­pore’s pro­duce, which in­cludes eggs and veg­eta­bles, the au­thor­i­ties could al­low com­pa­nies to put the na­tional flag on their pack­ag­ing (De­mand for lo­cal pro­duce must match sup­ply: Amy Khor, July 19). We can then eas­ily iden­tify lo­cal pro­duce with­out hav­ing to read the small print.</p>
    <p>This im­pedes traf­fic flow and poses a road haz­ard.</p>
    <p>PUT FLAG ON LO­CAL PRO­DUCE</p>
    <p>Koh Juat Huang</p>
    <p>Tan Jia Hao</p>
